post_text:
Reminder: P-EBT Application Window Closes July 31. Pandemic EBT (P-EBT) can provide families with children up to $325 for groceries. The Minnesota Department of Human Services says as many as 150,000 families may be eligible for these additional food assistance benefits. The application is available in Hmong, Russian, Somali, Spanish, and Vietnamese. The deadline has been extended to July 31. Please share this message with your community so families can apply at https://mn.p-ebt.org.

For help applying, families can call 651-431-4050 or 800-657-3698, Monday-Friday from 8 a.m. - 4 p.m.

post_text:
Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals. The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit.
Learn more at: www.mn.p-ebt.org

post_text: Here's a project Ms. Sipple's and Mrs. Hallman's class did during the final week of distance learning. They had an Interactive Read Aloud time and she read a story to the students called My Name is Sangoel by Karen Lynn Williams and Khadra Mohammed. In the story Sangoel moved to America from his homeland of Sudan. He was very proud of his name that had been handed down from his father and grandfather. Many people in America mispronounced his name and that made Sangoel feel sad. He came up with a plan to help others with the pronunciation. Sangoel drew a picture showing a sun and a soccer goal, which meant the pronunciation of his name was (sun-goal). I told the fourth grade students they could draw a picture showing how to pronounce their first, middle, or last name. #wegotthis

post_text: Here's a look at what's going on at school today: teachers are hard at work planning distance learning, kitchen staff are preparing meals for tomorrow, and a few staff members taking a break with a socially distanced walk. #wegotthis

post_text: Mrs. Attig and Mrs. Samp were out helping deliver meals in Albert Lea today. We'll be adding meal pick-up locations in Conger, Freeborn, and Wells for next week. Look for a new survey to come out tomorrow regarding next week's meal needs.
